/target/
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
CLAUDE.local.md

# Local credentials. Only redacted templates may be tracked.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
!.env.*.example
secrets.toml
credentials.json
!secrets.toml.example
!credentials.json.example

# ── One-repo membrane: solo artifacts evicted by the artifact-map audit ──────
# (task-20260623-feeb, ADR-133). These classify `solo` in
# .cosmon/artifact-map.toml — regenerable / local-only state that must never be
# tracked or shipped. Gitignored so a stray `git add` cannot silently re-track
# them; scripts/artifact-map-audit.py turns CI red if one reappears in the index.
mutants.out/
mutants.out.old/
.wrangler/
# Retired deny-by-default membrane machinery (ADR-127 → superseded by ADR-133).
# Kept on disk as a LOCAL input to `cs release-audit`'s Bucket-3 detectors, but
# never tracked: the allowlist enumerates the whole shipping frontier and
# release-rules carries confidential client/domain literals — neither can ship
# under the one-repo model.
.cosmon/release-allowlist.toml
.cosmon/release-rules.toml
.cosmon/events.jsonl

# Gas Town runtime state (auto-generated, session-specific)
.runtime/
.beads/redirect

# Paper build artifacts (keep .pdf — auto-committed by lefthook)
docs/paper/*.aux
docs/paper/*.bbl
docs/paper/*.blg
docs/paper/*.fdb_latexmk
docs/paper/*.fls
docs/paper/*.log
docs/paper/*.out
docs/paper/*.synctex.gz

# Cosmon residence (ADR-055, task-20260420-5ad6 migration zero):
# cosmon-the-repo is a `team` residence — narration lives on the orphan
# branch `cosmon/state`, not on `main`. `.cosmon/state/` is entirely
# gitignored here; the team-residence branch is where the shared memory
# lives under git.
.cosmon/registry.sqlite
.cosmon/registry.sqlite-journal
.cosmon/registry.sqlite-wal
.cosmon/*.lock
.cosmon/*.tmp
.cosmon/state/
.cosmon/state.next/
.cosmon/state.prev/
.cosmon/migration-manifest.pre.json
.worktrees/

# Instance OIDC identity + deploy/handover state (ADR-113 §9c): confidential
# INSTANCE data (sub=tenant_auditor@tenant-demo), never published. Extends the
# .cosmon/state/ ignore discipline above to deploy and handover snapshots.
**/deploy/state/
dist/**/state/

# Sovereign LPTHE build artifacts (scripts/lpthe, delib-20260705-7288 C2).
# The static musl binary + the versioned tarball are ephemeral build output —
# never tracked (binary-blob gate B1) and fully reproducible from source via
# scripts/lpthe/build-cs-musl.sh. The pinned BLAKE3 lives in the molecule's
# outcomes.md + the shipped MANIFEST.txt, not in git.
dist/lpthe/
dist/cosmon-lpthe-*.tar.gz

# Client correspondence + per-tenant handover/onboarding bundles
# (task-20260605-3db0, ADR-117 §4·c). These are one-to-one deliverables and
# letters (a signed letter of intent lived in correspondance/), never part of
# the public substrate. Evicted from the tree; gitignored so a future bundle
# cannot be silently re-tracked. Generic onboarding belongs in docs/, not here.
correspondance/
dist/*-handover/
docs/tenant-demo/

# Tenant-Demo strace traces (contain sensitive syscall data — review before sharing)
tenant-demo-traces/

# Phase 2 raw traces (pre-sanitization — sanitized copies live in evidence/traces-phase2/)
phase2-traces-raw/

# Phase 2b raw traces (contain API keys in network syscalls — NEVER commit)
phase2b-traces-raw/

# ILB demo rehearsal scratch dirs (smoke reports + bound /workspace traces)
.ilb-rehearsal/
.ilb-video-demo/
.addl-rehearsal/

# Synapse e2e demo: bind-mounted Synapse data dir — contains the generated
# homeserver.yaml (holds registration_shared_secret + signing keys),
# SQLite DB, media repo. Disposable, test-only, never commit.
docker/synapse-e2e/synapse-data/

# Swift Package Manager build artefacts (CosmonKit and siblings under apps/).
apps/**/.build/
apps/**/.swiftpm/
dist/l1-brew-tap/out/

# strace traces — regenerated by dist/rpp-live/strace-harness.sh
dist/rpp-live/strace-output/

# cosmon-remote cross-compiled binaries (task-20260522-aad5).
# Built locally by `just dist-binaries` and COPYed into the
# cosmon-rpp-adapter image at build time. The 24 MB are part of the
# *image*, not the *source* — but we keep the directory itself tracked
# (via a README.md) so the Dockerfile's `COPY --from=builder
# .../assets/binaries/` always finds the path. The binary files are
# the only thing actually ignored.
crates/cosmon-rpp-adapter/assets/binaries/**/cosmon-remote

# Mid-flight scaffolding — throwaway artefacts an agent or operator writes
# while thinking (mock-ups, sketches, micro-apps, JSON scratchpads). Never
# tracked. See docs/guides/scratch-convention.md (source: delib-20260523-fc0b).
scratch/

# insta pending snapshots — `*.snap.new` is the unaccepted output of a failing
# snapshot test. It must never be committed: doing so freezes a stale golden
# (the real `.snap` stays unrefreshed) and the test then fails forever. Two
# such strays (`help__root.snap.new`, `cs_help_tree.snap.new`) had shipped the
# `cs stitch` drift this way until 2026-05-28. Accept with `cargo insta accept`.
*.snap.new
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock

# mdBook build output for docs.noogram.org (docs/book/book/) — generated by
# `mdbook build docs/book`, never source. The tracked source lives in
# docs/book/src/ + docs/book/book.toml. (task-20260616-9c0b, Phase E.)
docs/book/book/

# Namespace-reservation packaging build outputs (regenerated by the verify
# commands in packaging/RESERVE-NAMES.md — never committed).
packaging/pypi/dist/
packaging/pypi/*.egg-info/
packaging/npm/*.tgz

# ── Membrane purge (task-20260616-66c1, B2) ───────────────────────────────
# Private surfaces evicted from the tracked tree ahead of the public release
# (parent: delib-20260616-0f4f filter-repo-first; sibling: task-20260616-cc22).
# Each line below is a real leak in the published tree; gitignored so a future
# `cs reconcile` / stray copy cannot silently re-track it. Same discipline as
# the `.cosmon/state/` ignore above (derived views of private state never ship).

# Root surface projections — auto-generated views of the operator's PRIVATE
# molecule backlog (.cosmon/state/, itself gitignored). They leak client names,
# meeting notes, the operator $PATH, and the entire private molecule graph
# (ids, workers, blocking edges). A public clone regenerates them empty via
# `cs reconcile` against its own state.
/STATUS.md
/ISSUES.md
/IDEAS.md
/DELIBERATIONS.md

# Private molecule declaration/artifact directory — the runtime sibling of
# .cosmon/state/. Tracked copies were old delib/idea artifacts (private
# panel responses, 'tenant_auditor-vm-cutover', …). Runtime reads still work
# (.cosmon/molecules/*.toml is read in-process); only tracking is removed.
.cosmon/molecules/

# Foreign private founding theses (neurion, topon) that landed at the cosmon
# root by stray import (ADR-013). Their canonical homes are their own repos.
/THESIS_NEURION.md
/THESIS_TOPON.md

# Operator-private tailnet infrastructure — real tailnet name, physical
# address, client roster, prod topology. Source-of-truth is the Tailscale
# console (+ git history); cross-referenced from mailroom, where it belongs.
/configs/tailscale/

# Stray editor/build temp siblings (e.g. CHANGELOG.md.tmp).
*.tmp

# ── Operator-private surfaces held off the public tree (release scrub
# task-20260713-b533). These either carry load-bearing operator/fund identity
# literals whose removal would defeat the file's purpose (.mailmap keys), or are
# operator-machine-specific glue / one-shot client-evidence tooling that inlines
# the confidential codebook (ADR-127 §6 — the detector must not re-leak). They
# stay on disk for local use; they simply never ship. Cf. scrub-log for rationale.
.mailmap
scripts/sanitize-traces-phase2.sh
scripts/sanitize-traces-phase2b.sh
scripts/drainage-tick.sh
cargo-scratch/
confidential-*.txt

# ── Publication sweep (task-20260714-bd06, pre-mortem I1). Backup/scratch and
# machine-local editor state that carried no public value and slipped into the
# index. Gitignored so a stray `git add` cannot re-track them; the legacy
# `.cosmon/ops/` molecule layout was relocated out of the public tree.
.obsidian/workspace.json
apps/ios-pilot/project.yml.bak
apps/ios-pilot/project.yml.new
.cosmon/ops/

# release-resync: real OIDC instance bindings are deployment data, never published
crates/cosmon-rpp-adapter/deploy/state/**/oidc-identity.toml
!crates/cosmon-rpp-adapter/deploy/state/**/oidc-identity.toml.example
